SIg-17 is a Special Interest Group of [http://www.resna.org/index.php RESNA] (Rehabilitation Engineering and Assistive Technology Society of North America). This group provides a forum for individuals interested in internationally appropriate assistive technology.

The main focus of this group has been [http://www.pitt.edu/AFShome/e/l/elast10/public/html/SIG17/ps.html Project Sore Butts], an effort to address the problem of pressure ulcers as they affect individuals in developing countries. Sorebutts has also held several wheelchair cushion design contests. A paper presenting the results of the [http://www.pitt.edu/AFShome/e/l/elast10/public/html/SIG17/cushion00/SoreButts2000Summary.pdf 2000 Cushion Design Contest] contains information and images of several wheelchair cushions.

Sig-17 and Sorebutts have also started developing alternative and augmentative communication strategies and held a [http://www.pitt.edu/AFShome/e/l/elast10/public/html/SIG17/post1996.html pressure sore prevention poster contest]in 1996.

